Explanation:

The solution uses a while loop to iterate through the digits of the input number. For each digit, it checks if it is even (divisible by 2). If a digit is even, the count is incremented. After processing all digits, the function returns the final count. The time complexity is O(log(n)) because the loop iterates through the digits of the number, which is log(n) in terms of the number of digits. The space complexity is O(1) because the function only uses a constant amount of space for the count variable. The energy implications are low because the algorithm is efficient and requires minimal resources.

